    "body": "## Summary\n\nThe Marlin NVFP4 kernel converts weight scales to a special S0E5M3 format by multiplying by `2^7`, assuming the MSB is always 1 for non-zero values. However, some models (e.g., those with `global_scale=1`) produce small scale values that violate this assumption. On BF16, the exponent widening in `dequant_fp8_scales` interprets these as ~2^(-112), causing underflow to zero and garbled output.\n\n**Fix:** Rescale weight scales in Python by a power-of-2 factor so all non-zero values satisfy the MSB=1 assumption after `* 2^7`, then compensate by dividing `global_scale` accordingly. This avoids any kernel modification.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Add `_nvfp4_compute_scale_factor` to compute the rescaling factor  \n- Apply rescaling in `nvfp4_marlin_process_scales` and compensate in `global_scale`  \n- Support shared scale factor across experts for MoE layers  \n\n## Test Plan\n\nTested with [GLM-4.7-Flash-NVFP4](https://huggingface.co/GadflyII/GLM-4.7-Flash-NVFP4) on RTX 4090:\n\n- **BF16:** GSM8K 5-shot accuracy = 81.3%, 0% invalid (was garbled output before fix)\n\nRelated #34694",
